title: English ship Charles (1632)
text:
Charles was a 44-gun <a href="second%20rate">second rank</a> <a href="ship%20of%20the%20line">ship of the line</a> of the <a href="Kingdom%20of%20England">English</a> <a href="history%20of%20the%20Royal%20Navy%20%28before%201707%29">navy</a>, built by <a href="Peter%20Pett">Peter Pett</a> at <a href="Woolwich">Woolwich</a> and launched in 1632.
"Charles" was renamed "Liberty" in 1649. She ran aground and was wrecked off <a href="Harwich">Harwich</a>, <a href="Essex">Essex</a> in October 1650.
